CommentTitle:
If you regulate legal gun ownership, it will make it harder for people to attain illegal weapons as well.
If you aren't allowed to store both the gun, and firing pin in the same location, if someone breaks in and steal your gun.. it's just a paperweight.
As a Swed, I have NEVER felt the need to own a gun.. and I have lived in some of the most ruff parts of Stockholm (Tensta, Hallonbergen). And I have had break-ins as well.
I have been active in the home guard, and done my military service, so I know how to handle a gun. 
Unless you are in the military, police, or a hunter, you don't need a gun. and the military should keep the guns on base, and police and hunters should have strict laws to follow when storing their guns at home.
